<!--Combinators are also type of selectors.-->
<!--Combinators are used when there is a parent child relation.-->
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
    <title>Child Selector</title>
    <style>
        .header>h1>span{
            background-color: rgb(168, 107, 225);
        }
        .main{
            background-color: burlywood;
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
    <div class="header">
        <h1>One <span>ONE</span></h1>
        <h2>Two</h2>
        <h3>Three</h3>
        <hr>
    </div>
    <div class="main">
        <h1>One</h1>
        <h2>Two</h2>
        <h3>Three</h3>
        <hr>
    </div>
    <div class="footer">
        <h1>One <span>ONE</span></h1>
        <h2>Two</h2>
        <h3>Three</h3>
        <hr>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
<!--Child Selector is used when we want to apply
Child Selector is represented by using '>' operator.
By using this selector we can apply styles Only for direct childs.
-->
